.TH ATLAS SIMPLE SHELL PROJECT "04 APRIL 2024" "1.0" "THE SIMPLE SHELL"
.SH THE SIMPLE SHELL
A simple shell, also known as a command-line interface, is a program that allows users to interact with an operating system by typing commands into a terminal or console.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Simple Shell is a program that interprets user commands and verifies paths to execute them. If the paths are invalid, it restarts the loop.
.SH USAGE EXAMPLES
.TP
.B $ /bin/ls
List the contents of a directory
.SH SEE ALSO
$ ls
$ exit
